Once upon a time, Craig Whitmore <lennon@igrin.co.nz> said:
>To my Knowledge 9789MB Not Equal 10.2Gig
No, but
9789 MB (1024 * 1024 bytes) = 10264510464 bytes
10264510464 bytes = 10.2 GB (1000 * 1000 * 1000 bytes)
Disk makers decided disks didn't sound big enough so they redefined the
terms.
